## 🌟 Code-Driven Dynamism Test (Completed)

I've just added three major changes across your codebase—**entirely in Python code**—to prove the documentation updates itself:

1.  **Feature Update**: Added a [deactivate_user](file:///e:/AutoCodeDoc/doc_automation_platform/backend/app/services/user_service.py#39-56) method to the **Service Layer**.
2.  **API Update**: Added a new **DELETE** route to the **Users API**.
3.  **Schema Update**: Added a **last_login** field to the **User Model**.

## 🛡️ Doc-Health: Preventing "Fucked" Documentation

I've implemented a two-part safety system to ensure your documentation never gets out of sync:

1.  **Code-Native Descriptions**: Descriptions for `last_login`, `bio`, etc., are now moved inside the code itself using `Field(description="...")`. This means the code *is* the source of truth.
2.  **Integrity Guard**: I've provided a script to catch undocumented fields:
    ```bash
    .\venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts/check_doc_sync.py
    ```
    ## 💊 Headache Protections (Edge Case Solved)

I've fortified the automation to handle real-world developer scenarios without further setup:

1.  **Automatic Discovery**: Any new class you add to [models/user.py](file:///e:/AutoCodeDoc/doc_automation_platform/backend/app/models/user.py) (like [Address](file:///e:/AutoCodeDoc/doc_automation_platform/backend/app/models/user.py#4-9)) is automatically detected and documented—no manual list required.
2.  **Nested Models**: If one model uses another (e.g., [User](file:///e:/AutoCodeDoc/doc_automation_platform/backend/app/models/user.py#10-21) has an [Address](file:///e:/AutoCodeDoc/doc_automation_platform/backend/app/models/user.py#4-9)), the system documents both in a clear hierarchy.
3.  **Complex Types**: Types like `List[str]` or `Optional[Address]` are cleaned up to be readable, instead of showing messy internal Python paths.
4.  **Smart Defaults**: The system now distinguishes between **Required** fields and those with a **Default Factory** (like empty lists).

**Final Verification**: Refresh the "Database Schema" page to see the new **Address** entity and the **Tags** list appearing automatically!
